    "description_long": "This object is a vintage tabletop radio receiver with a rectangular wooden casing and a black front panel. The front features a large speaker grille on the left, a clear frequency display window with tuning markings, and a prominent round tuning knob on the right. The top and sides are finished in a polished wood veneer, while the back panel is perforated for ventilation and includes various ports and labels. The overall design is reminiscent of mid-20th-century radios, combining both functional and decorative elements. The object is compact and would typically be found on a shelf, desk, or countertop in an urban environment.",
